1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:05,000
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

2
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:14,200
(STUMBLES)

3
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:18,600
-Mum, my shoelaces.
-You can do it.

4
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:21,200
-Please.
-OK.

5
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:27,400
Two bunny ears,
loop around and pull together.

6
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:29,520
(SIGHS)

7
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:33,080
-Got it?
-I don't want to be here.

8
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:36,000
James!

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,640
I want you to pick an artwork
you like and tell me about it.

10
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:46,320
Art is a wonderful thing,
and I want to enjoy it with you. OK?

11
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:48,120
OK.

12
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:51,120
(DELICATE, LIGHT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

13
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:12,280
Wow!

14
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:14,240
-What do you see?
-Come.

15
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:17,960
-Sit here.
-OK.

16
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:24,840
(BUGLE BLOWS FAINTLY)

17
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:27,440
(MEN ROAR FAINTLY)

18
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:30,880
(MILITARISTIC INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

19
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:35,200
Before you towers
a terrifying scene of war -

20
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,160
thousands of horses' hooves
break the grassy ground

21
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:39,840
in a cavalry charge!

22
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,320
(HOOVES BEAT, MEN ROAR)

23
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:45,760
Soldiers sporting blood-red uniforms
ride with valour

24
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:48,040
in a fearless resolve to attack!

25
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:50,200
Some blow military bugles,

26
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:52,760
others raise their voice
in a war cry.

27
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:55,800
Mighty silver blades
are exalted above their heads.

28
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:59,080
Leading up front, a commander,
on a mighty white stallion.

29
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:01,400
The beast's eyes
were wide and ferocious,

30
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:04,360
every muscle and vein
pulsing through its skin.

31
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:08,639
The commander rides the steed high,
his face blazing with heroism,

32
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:12,480
but still in his eyes,
a glimmer of fear,

33
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:17,920
for at the front line,
survival is not guaranteed.

34
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:19,920
(LAUGHS JOYOUSLY)

35
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:25,160
(AUDIENCE MEMBER WHISTLES)

36
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,840
I'm so proud of you!

37
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,480
Can you describe that one to us
over there?

38
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:40,240
(DELICATE, LIGHT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

